Importance of Mark's article

"To find out the different tunes sent out by a vibrating system is a
 problem which may or may not be solvable in certain special cases,
 but it would baffle the most skillful mathematician to solve the
 inverse problem and to find out the shape of a bell by means of the
 sounds which it is cable of sending out."
 -Arthur Schuster, 1882.

